<TITLE> Dollar slides to 12-year low below 101 yen </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Tokyo, March 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The dollar tumbled to a 12-year low below 101 yen on Thursday, sliding on doubts about the effectiveness of the Federal Reserve's efforts to aid strained credit markets and limit the damage to the US economy. The dollar fell as far as 100.95 yen on trading platform EBS, the lowest since December 1995, before clawing back to near 101.20 yen The dollar dropped to a record low against a trade-weighted basket of currencies at 72.184, taking its losses so far this year to nearly 6 percent.
